  "title": "AWS Cloud Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role Overview</strong><br />We are looking for a AWS Cloud Engineer to join our dynamic team. In this role, you will design, implement, and manage scalable, secure cloud solutions that support a wide range of clients. You will work on large-scale cloud projects in regulated environments, applying your expertise to solve complex challenges.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities & Skills</strong></p><ul><li><p>Manage and operate AWS environments at scale, with strong hands-on experience in EC2, S3, VPC, Lambda, RDS, IAM, and CloudWatch.</p></li><li><p>Apply networking, security, and identity management best practices within AWS.</p></li><li><p>Lead complex cloud projects independently and collaboratively.</p></li><li><p>Communicate technical concepts effectively to diverse audiences.</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience with automation/configuration tools such as CloudFormation, Terraform, or Ansible.</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with Docker and Kubernetes is a plus.</p></li><li><p>Relevant AWS certifications are highly desirable.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Why Join Us</strong></p><ul><li><p>Work with cutting-edge technologies and architectures.</p></li><li><p>Contribute to meaningful projects that impact lives.</p></li><li><p>Thrive in a collaborative, inclusive, and innovative environment.</p></li><li><p>Enjoy competitive remuneration and comprehensive benefits.<br /></p><p></p><p><strong>Work Location:</strong> North <br /></p><p></p><p>(EA Reg No: 20C0312)</p><p>Please email a copy of your detailed resume to <strong>kayla@talentsis.com.sg</strong> for immediate processing.</p><p>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p></li></ul>",
